The paper deals with the task of sequencing image-caption pairs to form a coherent story, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes multiple approaches using machine learning models, which falls under the scope of cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the paper also discusses the application of temporal common sense in AI tasks, which is related to information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
